        - <span>BUSINESS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>In­vest­ment bank­ing firm AMTD In­ter­na­tional, which is dual-listed in New York and Sin­ga­pore, has pro­moted Mr Wil­liam Fung to chief ex­ec­u­tive, suc­ceed­ing Mr Calvin Choi.</p>
    <p>This is in ad­di­tion to Mr Fung’s cur­rent po­si­tion of group vice-pres­i­dent of the com­pany’s par­ent, Hong Kong-based AMTD Group. Mr Fung was AMTD In­ter­na­tional’s chief in­vest­ment of­fi­cer and head of as­set man­age­ment.</p>
    <p>Mean­while, Mr Choi and the vice-chair­man An­drew Chiu will step down from the com­pany’s board.</p>


